рҹҡҖ Getting Started
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/lilaofficium/Etl-prj-for-retail.git
cd Etl-prj-for-retail
git checkout upload-retail-prj


2. Set up a virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate       # macOS/Linux
.venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows


3. Install dependencies
install -r requirements.txt


4. Configure environment
Create a .env file in the project root with your database credentials:
envDB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=retail_db
DB_USER=your_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

вҡ пёҸ Never commit your .env file. It is already excluded via .gitignore.

5. Run the full pipeline
Run : main.py 
This will execute Bronze вҶ’ Silver вҶ’ Gold sequentially and print a summary after each layer.




6. Run individual layers
Run : layer.run_bronze   # Bronze only
Run : run_layer.run_silver   # Silver only
Run : run_layer.run_gold     # Gold only

 

